ivardefs.name: encounter
ivardefs.desc: Describes the clinical encounter or type of care that the document content is associated with.

ivardefs.name: event_
ivardefs.desc: This list of codes represents the main clinical acts, such as a colonoscopy or an appendectomy, being documented. In some cases, the event is inherent in the typeCode, such as a "History and Physical Report" in which the procedure being documented is nece

ivardefs.name: facilityType
ivardefs.desc: The kind of facility where the patient was seen.

ivardefs.name: period
ivardefs.desc: The time period over which the service that is described by the document was provided.

ivardefs.name: practiceSetting
ivardefs.desc: This property may convey specifics about the practice setting where the content was created, often reflecting the clinical specialty.

ivardefs.name: related_
ivardefs.desc: Related identifiers or resources associated with the DocumentReference.

ivardefs.name: sourcePatientInfo
ivardefs.desc: The Patient Information as known when the document was published. May be a reference to a version specific, or contained.

properties.desc: The clinical context in which the document was prepared.
